### [Psalms Chapter 130](../../../bib/kjv/psa130.htm#001.md)

[Psalms 130:1](../../../bib/kjv/psa130.htm#001.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_001">psa 130:1</span></span>

The penitent sinner's hope is in God's mercy only. ([Psa
130:1-8](../../../bib/kjv/psa130.htm#001).md)

depths--for great distress ([Psa 40:2](../../../bib/kjv/psa040.htm#002.md);
[Psa 69:3](../../../bib/kjv/psa069.htm#003).md).

[Psalms 130:3](../../../bib/kjv/psa130.htm#003.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_003">psa 130:3</span></span>

shouldest mark--or, "take strict account" ([Job
10:14](../../../bib/kjv/job010.htm#014.md); [Job
14:16](../../../bib/kjv/job014.htm#016).md), implying a confession of the
existence of sin.

who shall stand-- ([Psa 1:6](../../../bib/kjv/psa001.htm#006).md). Standing
is opposed to the guilty sinking down in fear and self-condemnation
([Mal 3:2](../../../bib/kjv/mal003.htm#002.md); [Rev
6:15-16](../../../bib/kjv/rev006.htm#015).md). The question implies a
negative, which is thus more strongly stated.

[Psalms 130:4](../../../bib/kjv/psa130.htm#004.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_004">psa 130:4</span></span>

Pardon produces filial fear and love. Judgment without the hope of
pardon creates fear and dislike. The sense of forgiveness, so far from
producing licentiousness, produces holiness ([Jer
33:9](../../../bib/kjv/jer033.htm#009.md); [Eze
16:62-63](../../../bib/kjv/eze016.htm#062.md); [Pe1
2:16](../../../bib/kjv/pe1002.htm#016).md). "There is forgiveness with
thee, not that thou mayest be presumed upon, but feared."

[Psalms 130:5](../../../bib/kjv/psa130.htm#005.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_005">psa 130:5</span></span>

wait for the Lord--in expectation ([Psa
27:14](../../../bib/kjv/psa027.htm#014).md).

watch for, &c.--in earnestness and anxiety.

[Psalms 130:7](../../../bib/kjv/psa130.htm#007.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_007">psa 130:7</span></span>

Let Israel, &c.--that is, All are invited to seek and share divine
forgiveness.

from all his iniquities--or, "punishments of them" ([Psa
40:12](../../../bib/kjv/psa040.htm#012), &c..md).

